          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How does scarcity thinking hold people back financially?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Scarcity thinking creates a zero-sum view of wealth where earning more feels impossible and spending feels inevitable. It leads to short-term decisions, avoidance of investment risk, and a passive relationship with income." }
